From becaddde55a51bf7b411c621721b80d4ede4b001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Thu, 11 Dec 2025 22:57:43 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 51/73] drm/panthor: Add CIX Sky1 GPU support

Port Sky1-specific initialization from vendor kernel 6.6 to
mainline 6.18 Panthor driver.

Sky1 uses arm,mali-valhall compatible and has:
- RCSU region at resource 0, GPU at resource 1
- Backup clocks (gpu_clk_200M, gpu_clk_400M)
- Core harvesting via RCSU register 0x304
- PHBA (Page-Based Hardware Attribute) setup before L2 power-on
- LS_MEM counter initialization

This preserves mainline Panthor power management while adding
the platform-specific register writes needed for Sky1.
